ture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aArt and society. 0aPorcelain industryxSocial aspectszChinaxHistory. 0aPorcelainxSocial aspectsxHistory. 0aPorcelain, ChinesexSocial aspectsxHistory. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh  a14th century.  aart and politics.  aart.  aartistic symbols.  aartistic traditions.  aartists.  acanton.  achina.  achinese porcelain.  acobalt ore.  across cultural exchange.  adesigns.  adiscussion books.  aeconomic shifts.  aegypt.  aengland.  aeurope.  aglobal art.  aglobal culture.  ahistorical.  aindia.  airaq.  ajapan.  ajava.  amerchant ships.  amexico.  amuslim art.  apersia.  aperu.  apilgrim art.  aporcelain.  areligion.  asocial identity.  asoutheast asia.  aspain.  atraditional porcelain.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094538840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945388423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520945388/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles